track_notes: There is parking at the trailhead on the south side of hwy 87 just before you enter into the town of Strawberry. There was a faint trail along the west ridgeline and up the mountain just north of Strawberry Mnt. Once on top the trail faded but there are plenty of game trails to follow. The vegetation is not bad on the whole route. The activation zone is flat with plenty of space. Great hike and summit.

This bushwhack had some tough sections and some easy sections.  It is beautiful forest hiking and you will almost surely be alone.  Some parts had thick ironwood growth making progress more challenging.  The Activation Zone is huge.  I was surprised to find a 4wd road at the summit, not sure where it came from but perhaps there is an easier way up?

The starting point begins on Hardscrabble Mesa Road. I recommend accessing from Pine - accessing from Strawberry reroutes around private property and is not well maintained and longer. 

The early part of the hike is a short steep bushwhack. Once you climb past the initial ascent it flattens out to an open hike. About three-quarters to the top this route merges with a UTV trail that leads to the summit. 

The activation zone is large and presents many opportunities for antenna deployment.
